The //tangent bundle// $$\T M=\T(M)$$ to a [[smooth manifold|Smooth manifold]] $$M^m$$ is the disjoint union $$\bigsqcup_{p\in M}\T_p M$$ of all tangent spaces to $$M.$$ This is itself a smooth $$2m$$-manifold: Start with an [[atlas|Atlas]] for $$M.$$ Over any coordinate chart $$(U,\varphi),$$ there is a bijection
$$
\mathrm D\varphi\colon\T U\to\varphi(U)\times\R^m\subseteq\R^{2m},
\quad\T_p U=\T_p M\ni\sum v_i\partial_i\mapsto (\varphi(p),v).
$$
We define the topology on $$\T M$$ by specifying that these maps $$\D\varphi$$ are [[homeomorphisms|Hom√∂omorphismus]]; they then form an atlas and define a [[smooth structure|Smooth structure]].

A section of this [[vector bundle|Vector bundle]] is a [[vector field|Vector field]]. {{Endomorphism field}}